{"cursor":"5322","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n{{Infobox company |logo = |type = Private |foundation = February 2005\n|location_city = San Francisco |location_country = USA |location =  |locations =  |key_people = Vassil\nMladjov (CEO, founder)  Sean Engmann (COO) |area_served = |industry =\n|SWOT analysis = |products = |services = |revenue = |operating_income =\n|net_income = |num_employees = |parent = |divisions = |subsid = |slogan = The\nEnterprise Social Platform |homepage = |dissolved = |footnotes = |intl =  }} The\nsoftware company 'Sharetronix LLC' in San Francisco, California, produces an\nenterprise social software suite, encompassing blogs, wikis, social networking,\nmicroblogging, real-time collaboration and document management. The company has\noffices in the United States, Europe, and Canada, with headquarters in Berkeley,\nCalifornia. Early in 2012, the company changed its name to Sharetronix.\n\nBlogtronix was founded in 2005 by Vassil Mladjov. Blogtronix\nEnterprise 1.5 was released in November 2006. Information World Review and\nCMSWire compared Blogtronix 1.5 favorably to Intel's SuiteTwo collaboration\nplatform, which was a combination of several different collaboration elements\nincluding Socialtext. Blogtronix 3.5 was debuted Nov\n16â20, 2009, at the Web 2.0 Expo in New York City. Notable clients\ninclude Thomson-Reuters, Red Herring, and\nTelus. In 2008 and 2009, Blogtronix was included in the Gartner\nReporting Magic Quadrant for Social Software [http://my.gartner.com/portal/-\nserver.ptopen=512&objID=260&mode=2&PageID=3460702&resId=1213315&ref=QuickSearch-\n&sthkw=blogtronix+magic+quadrant Gartner Reports] Gartner listed\nBlogtronix as a \"social software vendor\" in its \"Collaboration and Social\nSoftware Vendor Guide\" for 2009. http://my.gartner.com/portal/server.pt?ope-\nn=512&objID=260&mode=2&PageID=3460702&resId=890012&ref=QuickSearch&sthkw=blogtr-\nonix In December 2009, Blogtronix was named to Red Herring's Global 100\nfinalist list. [http://redherring.com/Home/26265 Red Herring: Global\n100]\n\nThe company sponsors an open-source microblogging social software platform\ncalled [http://developer.sharetronix.com Sharetronix Open Source]. Sharetronix\ncites that it powers over 50,000 communities in over 170 countries and is\navailable in 33 languages.\n","linknr":215,"url":"Blogtronix","recorded":1375088065,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Blogtronix&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Blogtronix&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fe/Unbalanced_scales.svg/45px-Unbalanced_scales.svg.png","/wiki/Wikipedia:Conflict_of_interest","/wiki/Wikipedia:Cleanup","/wiki/Wikipedia:Neutral_point_of_view","/wiki/Talk:Blogtronix","/wiki/File:Btxlogo.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/c/c1/Btxlogo.png","/wiki/Types_of_business_entity","/wiki/San_Francisco","/w/index.php?title=Vassil_Mladjov&action=edit&redlink=1","/w/index.php?title=Sean_Engmann&action=edit&redlink=1","http://www.sharetronix.com/","/wiki/San_Francisco","/wiki/California","/wiki/Enterprise_social_software","/wiki/Wikis","/wiki/Social_networking","/wiki/Microblogging","/wiki/Collaboration","/wiki/Document_